 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of kinematic motion. Two complementary approaches are defined.
     One is defined as interpolation between a sequence of kinematic states.
     The other is defined by a set of 3D paths that control the motion
     of individual links.
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>definition of a kinematic motion as a sequence of discretised positions and orientations;</li>
   <li>definition of motion of one or several objects in 3D space along paths, coordinated by a parameter;</li>
   	  <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="b_spline_geometry:1_scope">B spline geometry</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1801;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:1_scope">Contextual shape positioning</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1027;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="kinematic_state:1_scope">Kinematic state</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1798;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="parametric_representation:1_scope">Parametric representation</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1813.</li>
 </inscope>

